    "context": "The Star Ferry has crossed Victoria Harbour since 1888. It links Tsim Sha Tsui (Kowloon) to Central and Wan Chai on Hong Kong Island. The upper deck costs a little more but the view is one of the best in the world. Trips take about 8 minutes.",
    "cultural_note": "The Star Ferry (天星小輪) has crossed Victoria Harbour since 1888, but its most turbulent moment came in 1966, when a proposed 5-cent fare increase sparked protests and several nights of rioting in Kowloon. This is now seen as the first stirring of a distinctly Hong Kong political consciousness, separate from both colonial Britain and mainland China. The rise went ahead, but only on first class. The ferry still runs.",
